COPY target/user-service.jar app.jar
ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar","/app.jar"]
Build image:
docker build -t user-service 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------.
🚀 4. Push to Docker Registry

👉 Store images in a central place
Example:
docker tag user-service myrepo/user-service
docker push myrepo/user-service

👉 Registry = Docker Hub / AWS ECR
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
☸️ 5. Deployment using Kubernetes

👉 Now we deploy microservices into Kubernetes cluster

Steps:
1. Create Deployment
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
2. Create Service
kind: Service

👉 This ensures:

Load balancing( means trying to maintain balance number of request for each server / trying to serve equal number of request for each pod / server etc)
Kubernetes Service distributes traffic:
Client → Service → Pod1 / Pod2 / Pod3
➡ No single pod overload
------------------------
Auto-scaling  ( means increasing servers/instances based on the demand of increase in request and reducing when there is no demand of request)
-------------------------------------
Self-healing  ( means 
If a pod crashes:
Pod1 ❌ → Kubernetes creates new Pod1 ✅
🔹 Auto Restart
Failed containers are restarted automatically
🔹 ReplicaSets
👉 Ensures required number of pods always running
Desired = 3 pods  
Running = 2 → K8s creates 1 more
